Claims Claims : 1. A system for services management, the system comprises: a plurality of user devices to provide an interactive interface to the user; a service management unit, the service management unit comprising of a user interface unit, a user registration and authentication unit, a service provider professional database, a user database, an external gateway interface unit and a processing unit; a communication network providing communication link between a plurality of the user devices and the service management unit. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the plurality of user devices to provide an interactive interface to the user includes mobile phone, PDA, a user terminal, portable computer device etc. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, user interface unit of the service management unit provides interface to communicate between the plurality of user devices and the service management unit. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the user registration and authentication unit identify, register and authenticate a plurality of users by receiving user details through user interface unit, provided by the user through the interactive interface on the user device. 5. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the service provider professional database maintains the complete details of the plurality of service provider professional along with classification of the plurality of service provider professional based on a plurality of service categories and subcategories. 6. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the user database maintains the complete details of the plurality of users along with classification of the plurality of services availed by the plurality of users based on a plurality of service categories and subcategories. 7. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the external gateway interface unit provides interface to the user to make recompensation through selected recompensation option. 8. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the processing unit is configured to perform presenting of plurality of service category to the at least one user; enabling the user to select category of service based on his/her choice/interest; enabling the user to select subcategory of the selected category of service; 

 accepting the task details provided by the user; determining the service location; booking instantly available service provider professional, if user confirms the same; posting the task to get quotes, if user confirms the same; optimizing, based on parametric inputs received from user, the list of the service provider professional from whom quotes are received; enabling the user to select service provider professional; comparing the selected service provider professionals profiles by setting parameters provided by user to highlight the most appropriate service provider based on criteria provided by the user; allowing communication, upon acceptance of a service provider professional by the user, by providing communication details of service provider professional to the user; upending the user with the hire summery; directing the user for recompensation through external gateway interface unit; presenting the task summery to the selected service provider professional; updating the task summery based on the action performed by the service provider professional; 

 notifying the system controller, administrator, two nominees given by the user and to the police, if emergency alert is activated; enabling the user to rate and review the service provided by the service provider professional further to the completion of the task. 9. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the service management unit is an embedded system configured on FPGA / CPLD. 10. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the processor of the service management unit is an embedded processor configured on FPGA / CPLD. 1 1 . The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein, the service management unit can be a server system incorporating various databases. 12. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the user includes the customers, users looking forward to hire services, service seekers, service providers, contractors and people at large. 13. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the location of the user be detected automatically. 14. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the user is prompted to provide the input detailing the location of the user or the location in which the user is looking forward to hire service or to provide service. 15. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein a user is allowed to write and post his/her requirement such as but not limited to the job required to be done or the type of services required. 16. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the parametric input includes the parameter such as radius distance, experience, price and review etc. 17. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the system provides complete profile of the service provider on request. 18. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the user is enabled to select a service provider based on the user's choice of the services required by presenting the user with at least one option of choosing the category and posting a request that will be received by all service providers in that category. 19. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the process of compare profile includes comparing the profile details such as location of the service provider, experience, price of the service of the service provider etc. 20. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the user is allowed to hire the service provider by setting the input such as the service required, the day and time at which the service required, the location and space where the service required. 21 . The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the hire summery includes date, time of hire, when user wants the service provider to visit their house recompensation of the service hired, selected recompensation option etc. 22. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein upon activation of the emergency feature by the user, it notifies to the system controller and administrator, to two nominees given by the user and to the police. 23. The system as claimed in claim 1 wherein the task summery is updated based on the action taken by service provider professional wherein the action includes task in progress, task rescheduling, task cancelation, task completion. 24. A method for services management, the method comprising steps of: identifying, registering and authenticating a plurality of users by receiving user details through user interface unit, provided by the user through the interactive interface on the user device; 

 presenting plurality of service category to the at least one user through the interactive interface on the user device; enabling the user to select category of service based on his/her choice/interest through the interactive interface on the user device; enabling the user to select subcategory of the selected category of service based on his/her choice/interest through the interactive interface on the user device; accepting through user interface unit, the task details provided by the user through the interactive interface on the user device; determining the service location; booking instantly available service provider professional, if user confirms the same; posting the task to get quotes, if user confirms the same; optimizing, based on parametric inputs received from user, the list of the service provider professional from whom quotes are received; enabling the user to select service provider professional based on his/her choice/interest through the interactive interface on the user device; comparing the selected service provider professionals profiles by setting parameters provided by user to highlight the most appropriate service provider based on criteria provided by the user; 

 allowing communication, upon acceptance of a service provider professional by the user, by providing communication details of service provider professional to the user; upending the user with the hire summery; directing the user for recompensation through external gateway interface unit; presenting the task summery to the selected service provider professional through the interactive interface on the user device; updating the task summery based on the action performed by the service provider professional; notifying the system controller, administrator, two nominees given by the user and to the police, if emergency alert is activated; enabling the user to rate and review the service provided by the service provider professional further to the completion of the task. 25. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the user includes the customers, users looking forward to hire services, service seekers, service providers, contractors and people at large. 26. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the location of the user may be detected automatically. 27. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the user is prompted to provide the input detailing the location of the user or the location in which the user is looking forward to hire service or to provide service. 28. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein a user is allowed to write and post his/her requirement such as but not limited to the job required to be done or the type of services required. 29. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the parametric input includes the parameter such as radius distance, experience, price and review etc. 30. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the system provides complete profile of the service provider on request. 31 . The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the user is enabled to select a service provider based on the user's choice of the services required by presenting the user with at least one option of choosing the category and posting a request that will be received by all service providers in that category. 32. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the process of compare profile includes comparing the profile details such as location of the service provider, experience, price of the service of the service provider etc. 33. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the user is allowed to hire the service provider by setting the input such as the service required, the day and time at which the service required, the location and space where the service required. 34. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the hire summery includes date, time of hire, when user wants the service provider to visit their house recompensation of the service hired, selected recompensation option etc. 35. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein upon activation of the emergency feature by the user, it notifies to the system controller and administrator, to two nominees given by the user and to the police. 36. The method as claimed in claim 24 wherein the task summery is updated based on the action taken by service provider professional wherein the action includes task in progress, task rescheduling, task cancelation, task completion.
